# Brand clone & sync

When the user asks to **clone**, **rebrand**, **white-label**, or **sync/migrate/update features** between this platform and another brand deploy:

1. Read **`.brand/README.md`** first (path split + commands).
2. Use the CLI — do not hand-copy the tree or invent a new tenancy model.

| Intent | Command |
|--------|---------|
| New brand site | `npm run brand:clone` |
| Pull platform updates into a clone | `npm run brand:sync -- pull --from <peer>` |
| Port clone platform work upstream | `npm run brand:sync -- push --to <peer>` |
| Preview drift | `npm run brand:diff -- --peer <peer>` |
| Leftover brand strings | `npm run brand:doctor` |

**Rules:**

- Prefer `--dry-run` before applying sync.
- Never overwrite **skin** (`brand.ts`, seeds, `public/`, theme hex) unless the user explicitly wants `--include-skin`.
- Keep Tailwind class names `cat4-*` across clones; only change hex in `tailwind.config.ts` + `brand.colors`.
- Path inventory SSOT: `.brand/paths.json`. Update it when adding new shared platform areas.
- Lineage: `.brand/lineage.json`. Deeper playbook: `.cursor/skills/cat4-platform/white-label.md`.
